&lt;p&gt;Rugby Place Based Team are looking to recruit a Band 5 nurse to deliver high quality, holistic nursing care to patients in their own home.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Nurses who work in our team have high standards, are highly motivated, compassionate, and enthusiastic and have an interest in developing their skills to care for patients with long term conditions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Successful applicants will need to have evidence of continuing professional development, be able to work as part of a team and have the ability to use their own initiative.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In return the applicant will be supported by relevant training and clinical supervision and will be joining a happy, supportive, hardworking team with a good sense of humour.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;These posts are based at The Orchard Centre, Rugby&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Minimum Qualification – RGN. Registered with the NMC&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicant must hold a full driving license and have access to their own vehicle (Car Lease scheme in operation).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;South Warwickshire NHS Foundation Trust promotes flexible working options on all appropriate positions and our managers welcome these discussions during the recruitment process.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
